---
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getAlbums } from '../lib/albums';

export const prerender = true;

const albums = getAlbums();
const featured = albums.find((a) => a.featured) ?? albums[0];
---

<Base title="About — Terrance McGovern" description="About landscape and astrophotographer Terrance McGovern.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 pb-20 pt-28 sm:px-8 sm:pt-32">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-light sm:text-4xl">About</h1>

    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[3fr_2fr]">
      <div class="space-y-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-fog sm:text-base">
        <p class="text-snow">
          I'm Terrance. I'm a facilities engineer for the United States Antarctic Program — the
          1,756th person to winter over at Amundsen-Scott South Pole Station, and as I write this,
          deployed to McMurdo Station for another austral winter.
        </p>
        <p>
          Wintering in Antarctica is something few people ever do. It's cold, dark, and about as
          remote as life gets. It's also beautiful in a way that's hard to explain, and these
          photos are my attempt to capture a sliver of it. Besides — being stuck at a small
          station with nowhere to go leaves plenty of time to build a website.
        </p>
        <p>
          Fair warning: I'm not a web developer, and this is my first site. I bought my camera
          just before deploying, so my best photos are still ahead of me. I'll also be adding
          shots from earlier travels — including plenty from underwater, since I'm a certified
          divemaster and have logged a few hundred dives. Those older shots are phone and
          dive-camera photos, more for the stories than for prints.
        </p>
        <p>
          More sections will appear as interests seize me. First up: a
          <a href="/gear/" class="text-snow underline decoration-fog/50 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-snow">Gear page</a>
          with what I actually use and stand by, and a
          <a href="/hikes/" class="text-snow underline decoration-fog/50 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-snow">Hikes page</a>
          to document the trips that put that gear to the test.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every photo here was shot on a real trip, in real weather, usually a long way from a
          road. If one of these images stays with you, I'd love to hear about it — a small number
          of prints will be available soon.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/prints/"
          class="inline-block border border-snow/80 px-6 py-3 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-snow transition-colors hover:bg-snow hover:text-night"
        >
          Ask about prints
        </a>
      </div>
      {
        featured && (
          <div>
            <Picture
              src={featured.cover}
              alt={featured.title}
              widths={[480, 800, 1200]}
              sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 40vw, 100vw"
              formats={['avif', 'webp']}
              fallbackFormat="webp"
              class="w-full object-cover"
            />
            <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-fog">From “{featured.title}”</p>
          </div>
        )
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
